  "body": "Previously, all references to closure arguments went to the argument before the one they should (e.g. to `arg1` when it was supposed to go to `arg2`). This was because the MIR builder did not account for the implicit arguments that come before the explicit arguments, and closures have one implicit argument - the struct containing the captures.\n\nThis is my test code and a diff of the MIR generated for the closure:\n\n``` rust\nlet a = 2i32;\nlet _f = |b: i32| -> i32 { a + b }:\n```\n\n``` diff\n--- old 2015-12-29 23:16:32.027926372 -0600\n+++ new 2015-12-29 23:16:42.975400757 -0600\n@@ -1,22 +1,22 @@\n fn(arg0: &[closure@closure-args.rs:8:14: 8:39 a:&i32], arg1: i32) -> i32 {\n     let var0: i32; // b\n     let tmp0: ();\n     let tmp1: i32;\n     let tmp2: i32;\n\n     bb0: {\n-        var0 = arg0;\n+        var0 = arg1;\n         tmp1 = (*(*arg0).0);\n         tmp2 = var0;\n         ReturnPointer = Add(tmp1, tmp2);\n         goto -> bb1;\n     }\n\n     bb1: {\n         return;\n     }\n\n     bb2: {\n         diverge;\n     }\n }\n```\n\n(If you're wondering where this text MIR output comes from, it's from another branch of mine waiting on https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/30602 to get merged.)\n",
